      "html": "<h3 id=\"what-do-live-local-and-offline-mean-in-the-header\">What do Live, Local and Offline mean in the header?</h3>\n<p><strong>Live</strong> means you are connected to the backend and changes save to the server. <strong>Local</strong> means the backend is not reachable or not configured, so changes are kept on the device. <strong>Offline</strong> means there is no connectivity; changes are queued and sync automatically when you reconnect.</p>\n<h3 id=\"will-i-lose-data-if-i-lose-signal-during-fieldwork\">Will I lose data if I lose signal during fieldwork?</h3>\n<p>No. Everything is written to the device first and added to a sync outbox. The header shows the pending count, and queued records sync automatically when connectivity returns. You can also tap the data-source pill to sync now.</p>\n<h3 id=\"why-can-t-i-grade-a-nonconformity-or-sign-the-report\">Why can&#39;t I grade a nonconformity or sign the report?</h3>\n<p>Those actions are <strong>lead-auditor only</strong> and are enforced on the server. If you are signed in as an auditor, the grade and sign-off controls are hidden. Verification of effectiveness and sign-off also require connectivity.</p>\n<h3 id=\"how-do-i-capture-photo-evidence\">How do I capture photo evidence?</h3>\n<p>Open the relevant checklist item or finding, choose to take a photo, capture the condition, and add a short note explaining why it matters. Timestamp and author attach automatically (plus GPS when available). Confirm the photo is linked to the correct item and shows a <em>synced</em> badge.</p>\n<h3 id=\"how-do-i-install-the-app-on-my-ipad\">How do I install the app on my iPad?</h3>\n<p>Open the site in Safari and add it to your Home Screen. It then runs full-screen as an installed PWA and works offline in the field.</p>\n<h3 id=\"can-i-use-the-app-without-a-backend\">Can I use the app without a backend?</h3>\n<p>Yes — choose <strong>Continue in offline demo mode</strong> at sign-in to explore the full workflow on local seed data.</p>\n<h3 id=\"how-do-i-switch-between-light-and-dark-mode\">How do I switch between light and dark mode?</h3>\n<p>Use the theme toggle in the header. The app also follows your device&#39;s system setting by default.</p>\n<h3 id=\"where-do-i-find-a-specific-record-or-template\">Where do I find a specific record or template?</h3>\n<p>Open the <strong>Records &amp; Documents Register</strong> in this knowledge base for a master list of EMS documents and records, plus templates such as the environmental policy.</p>",
