      "text": "Plan-Do-Check-Act ISO 14001:2015 follows the PDCA cycle inside the Annex SL high-level structure shared by modern ISO management standards: Plan — understand context, leadership commitment, risks and aspects, objectives. Do — provide support (resources, competence, communication, documented information) and operational control. Check — monitor, measure, evaluate compliance, audit internally, review with management. Act — correct nonconformities and continually improve. The clauses Clause Title What it covers (in brief) 4 Context of the organization Internal/external issues, interested parties, EMS scope. 5 Leadership Commitment, environmental policy, roles and responsibilities. 6 Planning Environmental aspects, compliance obligations, risks, objectives. 7 Support Resources, competence, awareness, communication, documented information. 8 Operation Operational planning and control, emergency preparedness. 9 Performance evaluation Monitoring, evaluation of compliance, internal audit, management review. 10 Improvement Nonconformity and corrective action, continual improvement. Trainovate stores clause identifiers and short titles only . It does not reproduce ISO requirements text. How Trainovate maps to the clauses Fieldwork checklists are organized by clause so coverage is traceable. EMS registers implement aspects (6.1.2), compliance obligations (9.1.2) and emergency preparedness (8.2). Findings & CAPA implement nonconformity and corrective action (10.2). Report & conclusions evidence performance evaluation and the audit's overall judgement. Programme schedules the audits that feed management review (9.3).",
