      "id": "fieldwork-and-evidence",
      "title": "Fieldwork & Evidence",
      "category": "using-the-app",
      "order": 1,
      "icon": "checklist",
      "summary": "How to answer checklist clauses and capture objective evidence on site.",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "lastUpdated": "2026-05-30",
      "readingMinutes": 1,
      "type": "doc",
      "html": "<h2 id=\"fieldwork-mode\">Fieldwork mode</h2>\n<p>Fieldwork presents one clause at a time so you can work one-handed while walking the site.</p>\n<ul><li><strong>Result buttons</strong> — Conform, Minor NC, Major NC, OFI, N/A in a sticky bottom bar.</li><li><strong>Progress</strong> — the bar tracks how many clauses are answered.</li><li><strong>Filters</strong> — jump to unanswered clauses or a specific section.</li><li><strong>Inline capture</strong> — add a note or photo without leaving the clause.</li><li><strong>Log finding</strong> — raise a nonconformity directly from a non-conforming clause.</li></ul>\n<h3 id=\"recommended-habits\">Recommended habits</h3>\n<ol><li>Confirm you are in the correct tenant, auditee and site.</li><li>Check the audit status before editing.</li><li>Sync before leaving reliable connectivity.</li><li>Answer every clause or mark it N/A with a reason — no silent gaps.</li></ol>\n<h2 id=\"evidence\">Evidence</h2>\n<p>Every audit finding must rest on <strong>objective evidence</strong>. Each evidence record should answer three questions:</p>\n<ul><li><strong>What</strong> was observed?</li><li><strong>Where and when</strong> was it observed?</li><li><strong>Who</strong> captured it?</li></ul>\n<h3 id=\"evidence-types\">Evidence types</h3>\n<table><thead><tr><th>Type</th><th>Use it for</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Photo</td><td>Conditions, labels, records, controls, locations.</td></tr><tr><td>Note</td><td>Interview responses, observations, sample references.</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<h3 id=\"photo-tips\">Photo tips</h3>\n<ul><li>Include enough surrounding context to understand the location.</li><li>Avoid people, private information or restricted areas unless authorized.</li><li>Retake blurry or poorly lit photos.</li><li>Add a note when the image contains specialized equipment or site-specific terms.</li></ul>\n<h3 id=\"sync-badges\">Sync badges</h3>\n<p>Each record shows its state: <strong>queued</strong>, <strong>syncing</strong> or <strong>synced</strong>. When offline, keep capturing normally — records sync automatically when connectivity returns.</p>",
