      "id": "aspects-and-impacts",
      "title": "Environmental Aspects & Impacts",
      "category": "iso-14001",
      "order": 2,
      "icon": "water_drop",
      "summary": "Identify environmental aspects, assess significance and record controls (cl. 6.1.2 / 8.1).",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "lastUpdated": "2026-05-30",
      "readingMinutes": 1,
      "type": "doc",
      "html": "<h2 id=\"aspect-vs-impact\">Aspect vs impact</h2>\n<ul><li>An <strong>aspect</strong> is an element of the organization&#39;s activities, products or services that can interact with the environment (for example, <em>discharge of wastewater</em>).</li><li>An <strong>impact</strong> is the resulting change to the environment (for example, <em>degradation of water quality</em>).</li></ul>\n<h2 id=\"determining-significance\">Determining significance</h2>\n<p>Assess each aspect using consistent criteria, typically combining:</p>\n<ul><li><strong>Severity / scale</strong> of the potential impact;</li><li><strong>Likelihood / frequency</strong> of occurrence;</li><li><strong>Legal and other obligations</strong> that apply;</li><li><strong>Interested-party concerns</strong>;</li><li>conditions: <strong>normal, abnormal and emergency</strong>.</li></ul>\n<p>Aspects that score above your threshold become <strong>significant aspects</strong> and must be controlled and considered when setting objectives.</p>\n<h2 id=\"what-to-record-per-aspect\">What to record per aspect</h2>\n<table><thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Activity / product / service</td><td>The source of the aspect.</td></tr><tr><td>Aspect</td><td>The interaction with the environment.</td></tr><tr><td>Impact</td><td>The environmental consequence.</td></tr><tr><td>Lifecycle stage</td><td>Acquisition, design, operation, end-of-life.</td></tr><tr><td>Condition</td><td>Normal / abnormal / emergency.</td></tr><tr><td>Significance</td><td>Rating against your criteria.</td></tr><tr><td>Controls</td><td>Operational controls in place.</td></tr><tr><td>Linked objective</td><td>If an objective addresses it.</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<h2 id=\"in-trainovate\">In Trainovate</h2>\n<p>Maintain this on the <strong>EMS</strong> tab under <em>Significant environmental aspects</em>. Each row carries a conformity result so the auditor can record whether controls are adequate and effective.</p>",
