      "text": "Aspect vs impact An aspect is an element of the organization's activities, products or services that can interact with the environment (for example, discharge of wastewater ). An impact is the resulting change to the environment (for example, degradation of water quality ). Determining significance Assess each aspect using consistent criteria, typically combining: Severity / scale of the potential impact; Likelihood / frequency of occurrence; Legal and other obligations that apply; Interested-party concerns ; conditions: normal, abnormal and emergency . Aspects that score above your threshold become significant aspects and must be controlled and considered when setting objectives. What to record per aspect Field Notes Activity / product / service The source of the aspect. Aspect The interaction with the environment. Impact The environmental consequence. Lifecycle stage Acquisition, design, operation, end-of-life. Condition Normal / abnormal / emergency. Significance Rating against your criteria. Controls Operational controls in place. Linked objective If an objective addresses it. In Trainovate Maintain this on the EMS tab under Significant environmental aspects . Each row carries a conformity result so the auditor can record whether controls are adequate and effective.",
