      "id": "quick-start",
      "title": "Quick Start (10 minutes)",
      "category": "getting-started",
      "order": 2,
      "icon": "bolt",
      "summary": "Run your first audit pass end to end in about ten minutes.",
      "version": "1.0.0",
      "lastUpdated": "2026-05-30",
      "readingMinutes": 1,
      "type": "doc",
      "html": "<h2 id=\"before-you-start\">Before you start</h2>\n<p>You need auditor credentials and, ideally, connectivity for the first load. If the backend is not configured, choose <strong>Continue in offline demo mode</strong> to use seed data.</p>\n<h2 id=\"1-sign-in\">1. Sign in</h2>\n<p>Open the app and sign in. Check the <strong>data-source pill</strong> in the header reads <strong>Live</strong> (or <strong>Local</strong> in demo mode).</p>\n<h2 id=\"2-confirm-the-audit-context\">2. Confirm the audit context</h2>\n<p>On <strong>Overview</strong>, confirm you are looking at the correct auditee, site and audit. Check the audit status before editing records.</p>\n<h2 id=\"3-open-the-audit\">3. Open the audit</h2>\n<p>On the <strong>Audit</strong> tab, record the <strong>opening meeting</strong>: scope, criteria, methods, confidentiality and schedule.</p>\n<h2 id=\"4-work-the-checklist\">4. Work the checklist</h2>\n<p>On <strong>Fieldwork</strong>, answer clauses one at a time:</p>\n<ol><li>Read the question and guidance.</li><li>Pick a result: Conform, Minor NC, Major NC, OFI or N/A.</li><li>Add a note and a photo where useful.</li><li>Tap <strong>Log finding</strong> on anything non-conforming.</li></ol>\n<h2 id=\"5-capture-evidence\">5. Capture evidence</h2>\n<p>On <strong>Evidence</strong>, confirm your photos and notes are attached to the right clause or finding and show a <strong>synced</strong> badge.</p>\n<h2 id=\"6-grade-findings\">6. Grade findings</h2>\n<p>On <strong>Findings</strong>, open each nonconformity, state it clearly, attach objective evidence, and (as lead auditor) set the <strong>grade</strong> and rationale. Open a corrective action with an owner and due date.</p>\n<h2 id=\"7-complete-the-ems-registers\">7. Complete the EMS registers</h2>\n<p>On <strong>EMS</strong>, record significant aspects, compliance obligations and emergency preparedness for the scope you audited.</p>\n<h2 id=\"8-close-and-report\">8. Close and report</h2>\n<p>On <strong>Audit</strong>, record the <strong>closing meeting</strong> and conclusions. On <strong>Report</strong>, clear the readiness checks and, as lead auditor, <strong>sign off</strong>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"9-sync\">9. Sync</h2>\n<p>Tap the data-source pill to push any queued changes. The pending count should reach zero.</p>\n<p>That&#39;s a full pass. For depth on any step, see the <a class=\"wiki-doclink\" data-doc=\"user-guide\" href=\"#\">Comprehensive User Guide</a>.</p>",
