      "text": "How to use this register This master list is modeled on documents and records commonly maintained by certified ISO 14001 programs. Use it as a document-control index: confirm each item exists, is current, has an owner, and has a retention period. Items marked Document are kept current and version-controlled; items marked Record are retained as evidence. Clause references are identifiers and short titles only. Retention periods are common defaults — set yours to match legal and contractual requirements. Clause 4 — Context Ref Document / Record Type Suggested owner Retention 4.1/4.2 Context & interested-parties analysis Document EMS manager Current + 1 cycle 4.3 EMS scope statement Document EMS manager Current 4.4 EMS manual / process map Document EMS manager Current Clause 5 — Leadership Ref Document / Record Type Suggested owner Retention 5.2 Environmental policy Document Top management Current + history 5.3 Roles, responsibilities & authorities Document Top management Current 5.1 Leadership commitment evidence (e.g. review minutes) Record EMS manager 3 years Clause 6 — Planning Ref Document / Record Type Suggested owner Retention 6.1.1 Risks & opportunities register Document EMS manager Current 6.1.2 Environmental aspects & impacts register + significance criteria Document EMS manager Current 6.1.3 Compliance obligations (legal) register Document Compliance lead Current 6.2 Environmental objectives & action plans Document EMS manager Current + 1 cycle Clause 7 — Support Ref Document / Record Type Suggested owner Retention 7.2 Competence matrix & criteria Document HR / EMS Current 7.2 Training records & certificates Record HR Employment + 3 yrs 7.3 Awareness / induction records Record HR 3 years 7.4 Communication plan & log (internal/external) Document/Record EMS manager 3 years 7.5 Document control / master list & change log Document Document controller Current Clause 8 — Operation Ref Document / Record Type Suggested owner Retention 8.1 Operational control procedures / work instructions Document Process owners Current 8.1 Permits-to-work / consents Record Site manager Per permit 8.1 Supplier / contractor environmental requirements Document Procurement Current 8.1 Lifecycle / design environmental criteria Document Engineering Current 8.1 Waste transfer & consignment notes Record Site manager 2–3 years 8.2 Emergency preparedness & response plans Document EHS lead Current 8.2 Emergency drill / test records Record EHS lead 3 years 8.2 Incident & spill reports Record EHS lead 3+ years Clause 9 — Performance evaluation Ref Document / Record Type Suggested owner Retention 9.1.1 Monitoring & measurement plan Document EMS manager Current 9.1.1 Monitoring results & calibration records Record Lab / engineering 3 years 9.1.2 Evaluation-of-compliance records Record Compliance lead 3+ years 9.2 Internal audit programme & plan Document Lead auditor Current + 1 cycle 9.2 Internal audit reports & checklists Record Lead auditor 3 years 9.2 Auditor competence & impartiality records Record Audit programme manager 3 years 9.3 Management review inputs & minutes Record Top management 3 years Clause 10 — Improvement Ref Document / Record Type Suggested owner Retention 10.2 Nonconformity & corrective-action register Record EMS manager 3 years 10.2 Root-cause analyses Record Action owners 3 years 10.3 Continual-improvement log Record EMS manager 3 years Audit-engagement records (ISO 19011 / 17021-1) Document / Record Type Owner Retention Audit programme Document Programme manager Current + 1 cycle Audit plan (per audit) Document Lead auditor 3 years Opening / closing meeting records Record Lead auditor 3 years Field checklists & evidence Record Audit team 3 years Findings & graded nonconformities Record Lead auditor 3 years Audit conclusions & recommendation Record Lead auditor 3 years Signed audit report Record Lead auditor 3+ years / per cycle Corrective-action verification records Record Lead auditor 3 years Where Trainovate produces these Trainovate generates and stores many of these records directly: checklists & evidence, findings & CAPA, the EMS registers (aspects, compliance, emergency), conclusions and the signed report. Maintain the document -type items (policy, procedures, registers' definitions, plans) in your document-control system and reference them here.",
